-- product_return_rates.sql
SELECT
  COALESCE(c.name, 'Uncategorized') AS category_name,
  COUNT(oi.item_id) AS total_items_sold,
  COUNT(DISTINCT CASE 
    WHEN r.return_id IS NOT NULL 
    AND r.status = 'approved'
    THEN oi.item_id 
  END) AS total_items_returned,
  ROUND(
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE 
      WHEN r.return_id IS NOT NULL 
      AND r.status = 'approved'
      THEN oi.item_id 
    END) * 100.0 / COUNT(oi.item_id),
    2
  ) AS return_rate
FROM
  order_items oi
  JOIN orders o ON oi.order_id = o.order_id
  JOIN products p ON oi.product_id = p.product_id
  LEFT JOIN categories c ON p.category_id = c.category_id
  LEFT JOIN returns r ON oi.item_id = r.item_id
    AND r.return_id = (
      SELECT return_id 
      FROM returns 
      WHERE item_id = oi.item_id 
      AND status = 'approved'
      ORDER BY return_date DESC 
      LIMIT 1
    )
GROUP BY
  COALESCE(c.name, 'Uncategorized')
ORDER BY
  category_name;
